Git= version Control in Team Porject Management

---

**Git First Time Setup Process**

1. Install Git:
Download and install Git from:
https://git-scm.com/

2. Check Git Version:
git --version

3. Set Username:
git config --global user.name "Your Name"

4. Set Email:
git config --global user.email "youremail@example.com"

5. Check Configuration:
git config --list

---


**Basic Git Workflow**

1. Create a File:
Example:
index.html

2. Check Status:
git status

3. Stage File:
git add .

4. Commit Changes:
git commit -m "Initial commit"

5. View Commit History:
git log or git log --oneline

6. Show Changes:
git diff

7. Reset Last Commit:
git reset --soft HEAD~1

8. Create Branch:
git branch feature

9. Switch Branch:
git checkout feature

10. Merge Branch:
git merge feature

---
feature = new branch name

git checkout feature

Meaning:
"feature" branch এ switch করো

---

Connect Existing Local Project to an Existing GitHub Repository

1. Open project folder in VS Code

2. Open terminal

3. Initialize Git:
git init

4. Add GitHub repository link:
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/your-repository-name.git

5. Check remote link:
git remote -v

6. Stage files:
git add .

7. Commit files:
git commit -m "Initial commit"

8. Push to GitHub:
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

9. Remove file from staging area:
git restore --staged filename

10. Remove all staged files:
git restore --staged .


---


**How to Uncommit**

1. Remove last commit but keep changes:
git reset --soft HEAD~1

2. Remove last commit and unstage changes:
git reset HEAD~1

3. Remove last commit and delete changes:
git reset --hard HEAD~1

4. Discard chnages/remove new changes code lines from file that not commited yet:
git restore file-name

